Fresh Pi session: PR DRAFTING ONLY.

Inputs:
- Prompt, approved use case, completed test-list history, TDD evidence, regression report, and review report: {{run.dir}}
- Worktree: {{run.worktree-dir}}

Goal:
Draft accurate pull request metadata for the accepted Canon TDD change.

Rules:
- Do not edit source code, call GitHub, or push.
- Summarize the actor outcome, implementation, scenarios completed, validation performed, refactoring decisions, and risks.
- Verify the worktree has committed changes ready to push.
- If the change alters a Tesseraft capability, ensure `STATUS.edn` and generated README status are truthful before passing.

Write:
- Title: {{run.dir}}/pr/pr-title.txt
- Body: {{run.dir}}/pr/pr-body.md
- Status: {{run.dir}}/pr/draft-status-{{run.round}}.json

Status:
{"status":"pass","summary":"PR metadata drafted","issues_file":null}

The body should include Summary, Use case, Test scenarios, Implementation notes, Validation, Refactoring, and Risks or follow-up.
